
In a scene reminiscent of summer camp, the boatmen carried their canoes down the ramp, positioned them on the banks of the Flint River, and waited for instructions. "Has anyone not been canoeing before?" asked Jim McDaniel, owner of the Flint River Outdoor Center in Thomaston. The boatmen, 59 businessmen and women from area Rotary Club chapters, listened impatiently while McDaniel proceeded with a lesson on the basics, including efficient paddling and navigating rapid water and rocks. 

